A couple have died in Mookgophong, Limpopo when a light airplane they were traveling in allegedly crashed on the hill next to a Game Lodge The deadly crash happened approximately at 13h00 today (Friday). Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe the spokesman for Limpopo PoliceÂ  has confirmed that both deceased were identified as Johannes Kemp (77) and his wife Angelina Kemp (66) from Volkrus, Ermelo from Mpumalanga. "The couple were allegedly visiting their son at the said Game Lodge when the accident happened. Unfortunately when the police and Rescue Team visited the scene the couple had died." Ngoepe said. Ngoepe added that the Civil Aviation Authority is investigate the cause of the crash.